comment:
* An instance of this class is passed as a parameter in various {@link WebChromeClient} action
 * notifications. The object is used as a handle onto the underlying JavaScript-originated request,
 * and provides a means for the client to indicate whether this action should proceed.

variables.name: mReceiver
variables.comment: This is the caller of the prompt and is the object that is waiting.

variables.name: mResult
variables.comment: This is a basic result of a confirm or prompt dialog.

methods.name: public final void cancel()
methods.comment: * Handle the result if the user cancelled the dialog.

methods.name: public final void confirm()
methods.comment: * Handle a confirmation response from the user.

methods.name: public final boolean getResult()
methods.comment: * @hide Only for use by WebViewProvider implementations

methods.name: private final void wakeUp()
methods.comment: Notify the caller that the JsResult has completed
